data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a group of chosen members of a government, which is responsible for advising and deciding on government policy

data.chText: 影子内阁（反对党中最重要的成员）
data.enText: the shadow Cabinet (= the most important members of the opposition party)
a piece of furniture with doors, drawers and/or shelves, that is used for storing or showing things
The china was displayed in a glass cabinet.

tr: a piece of furniture resembling a cupboard with doors and shelves and drawers
housing for electronic instruments, as radio or television
a storage compartment for clothes and valuables
persons appointed by a head of state to head executive departments of government and act as official advisers

value.def: A cabinet is a cupboard used for storing things such as medicine or alcoholic drinks or for displaying decorative things in.

example.ex: The star of my medicine cabinet is the humble aspirin...
example.tran: 我家药柜里的压箱宝要算是那不起眼的阿司匹林。

example.ex: He looked at the display cabinet with its gleaming sets of glasses.
example.tran: 他看着陈列柜,里面摆着几套晶莹剔透的玻璃杯。

value.def: The Cabinet is a group of the most senior ministers in a government, who meet regularly to discuss policies.

example.ex: The announcement came after a three-hour Cabinet meeting in Downing Street.
example.tran: 在唐宁街进行了长达3个小时的内阁会议后发布了这份公告。

trans: 内阁办公室(英国政府部门，负责内阁和文职部门的工作)
(首相或总统的)厨房内阁，私人顾问团(尤为记者用语，表示不满)
